         <caption>
			Positive Definite
		</caption>
         <para>
            <para.body>The dot product is positive definite because</para.body>
         </para>
         <math.display>
            <latex>\DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{x} } = \DotPr{ (x_1,\dots ,x_n) }{ (x_1,\dots ,x_n) } = x_{1}^{2} + \cdots + x_{n}^{2} \geq 0</latex>
         </math.display>
         <logic>
            <part.ref>theopart_DotProductNonDegenerate</part.ref>
         </logic>
         <caption>
			Non Degenerate
		</caption>
         <para>
            <para.body>The dot product operation is non-degenerate because <math>
                  <latex>\DotPr{ \Vect{x} }{ \Vect{x} } = 0</latex>
               </math> if and only if</para.body>
         </para>
         <math.display>
            <latex>x_{1}^{2} + \cdots + x_{n}^{2} = 0</latex>
         </math.display>
         <para>
            <para.body>Now this sum of squares is zero if and only if <math>
                  <latex>x_{i}^{2} = 0</latex>
               </math> for each <math>
                  <latex>1\leq i\leq n</latex>
               </math>. Now <math>
                  <latex>x_{i}^{2} = 0</latex>
               </math> if and only if <math>
                  <latex>x_i=0</latex>
               </math>, and this is equivalent to</para.body>
         </para>
         <para align="center">
            <para.body>
               <math>
                  <latex>(x_1,\dots ,x_n) = \Vect{x} = \Vect{0}</latex>
               </math>.</para.body>
         </para>
